<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE24B6A94BFDC2FDC0" bold="true" box="[151,588,565,590]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
Material studied. 
<typeStatus id="54E0F0FC81BB0DAE2552A948FE6EFDC3" box="[371,480,566,589]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Holotype</typeStatus>
f: JAVA
</emphasis>
, Soekaboemi (now Sukabumi), on tea (
<taxonomicName id="4C5B35DD81BB0DAE2000A94BFBD7FDC0" authority="Albers, 1850" authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1850" box="[1057,1113,565,590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bradybaenidae" genus="Thea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE2000A94BFBD7FDC0" box="[1057,1113,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Thea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B35DD81BB0DAE20B4A94BFA8EFDC0" box="[1173,1280,565,590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Theaceae</taxonomicName>
), no date, C. Bernard (BMNH): 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE254CA927FEF8FDFC" box="[365,374,601,626]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE255EA927FE06FDFC" box="[383,392,601,626]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="1.0">1</number>
adf (fg; with manuscript name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B35DD81BB0DAE26CAA924FC33FDFC" authority="Green" authorityName="Green" box="[747,957,601,626]" class="Insecta" family="Cerococcidae" genus="Cerochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardi">
<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE26CAA924FCE3FDFC" box="[747,877,601,626]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">C. bernardi</emphasis>
Green
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44E5E81BB0DAE24E6A900FC56FD18" blockId="144.[151,1437,565,1958]" box="[199,984,637,662]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE24E6A900FE29FD18" bold="true" box="[199,423,637,662]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Mounted material.</emphasis>
Body almost round, 
<quantity id="4CA3E3BB81BB0DAE26B3A900FD67FD1B" box="[658,745,638,662]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CA3E3BB81BB0DAE270EA900FC1DFD1B" box="[815,915,638,662]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" unit="mm" value="1.55">1.55 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44E5E81BB0DAE24E6A9DCFB16FA07" blockId="144.[151,1437,565,1958]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE24E6A9DCFEA0FD37" bold="true" box="[199,302,674,697]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Dorsum.</emphasis>
Eight-shaped pores of about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2659A9DCFD08FD34" box="[632,646,674,698]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.0">4</number>
sizes: (i) larger pores, each 13.0â€“ 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2020A9DCFBBFFD34" box="[1025,1073,674,698]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="13.5">13.5</number>
<date id="FFE5689E81BB0DAE2019A9DCFBD2FD34" box="[1080,1116,674,698]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
x 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE206FA9DCFBD2FD34" box="[1102,1116,674,698]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.0">8</number>
</date>
Âµm, present in a ring of 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2153A9DCFF3DFD50" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20â€“ 25</number>
around apex of each stigmatic pore band; (ii) a slightly smaller pore, each 11.0â€“ 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2010A9B8FBEEFD50" box="[1073,1120,710,734]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="12.5">12.5</number>
<date id="FFE5689E81BB0DAE2046A9B8FB07FD50" box="[1127,1161,710,734]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
x 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE205AA9B8FB07FD50" box="[1147,1161,710,734]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.0">8</number>
</date>
Âµm, each sunk in a deep indentation, in groups of 
<quantity id="4CA3E3BB81BB0DAE258EA994FD9CFC8C" box="[431,530,745,770]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2319" metricValueMax="1.3208" metricValueMin="1.143" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" unit="in" value="48.5" valueMax="52.0" valueMin="45.0">45â€“52 in</quantity>
centre of apex of each stigmatic pore band; also in a further ring just outside ring of largest pores; these becoming smaller (size (iii)) further from apical group, down to about 
<date id="FFE5689E81BB0DAE20E7A870FB62FCAB" box="[1222,1260,782,806]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20E7A870FB5AFCA8" box="[1222,1236,782,806]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="9.0">9</number>
x
</date>
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20D5A870FA8CFCA8" box="[1268,1282,782,806]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="6.0">6</number>
Âµm; and (iv) small pores, each 
<date id="FFE5689E81BB0DAE2540A84CFE0AFCC7" box="[353,388,818,841]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2540A84CFEE1FCC7" box="[353,367,818,841]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
x
</date>
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE25AAA84CFE17FCC4" box="[395,409,818,842]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="3.0">3</number>
Âµm, forming a lattice-like pattern, with seven radial bands on each side, a submedial circle of pores, divided medially by 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE25C9A828FE78FCE0" box="[488,502,854,878]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.0">4</number>
transverse bands and 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE26CFA828FD72FCE0" box="[750,764,854,878]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
longitudinal bands (see figure); very slightly smaller pores, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE24F3A804FF7BFC1C" box="[210,245,890,914]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.5">4.5</number>
x 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2532A804FEB8FC1C" box="[275,310,890,914]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.5">2.5</number>
Âµm, present sparsely in areas between lattice lines. Simple pores very sparse throughout, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE214AA804FA02FC1C" box="[1387,1420,890,914]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="1.5">1.5</number>
â€“ 2.0 Âµm wide. Cribriform plates small, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE26A4A8E0FD32FC38" box="[645,700,926,950]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8â€“10</number>
Âµm wide, in a single median group of 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2057A8E0FB08FC38" box="[1142,1158,926,950]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="9.0">9</number>
, each with median-sized micropores and a fairly broad margin. Dorsal setae extremely few, each setose, and mainly 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20ACA8BCFB15FC57" box="[1165,1179,962,985]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
Âµm long, but also with a single fleshy seta within apex of each stigmatic pore band. Tubular ducts short, each about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20BFA898FB34FC70" box="[1182,1210,998,1022]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="16.0">16</number>
Âµm long with many spines within cup-shaped invagination of outer ductule; of three widths: (i) a broad duct, each 4.0â€“ 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2124AF74FAA9FBAC" box="[1285,1319,1034,1058]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.5">4.5</number>
Âµm wide, present in lines parallel to small 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2620AF53FD82FBC8" box="[513,524,1069,1094]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.0">8</number>
-shaped pores bands, forming a reticulate pattern, and also in a group medially on posterior abdominal segments; (ii) ducts of intermediate width, each about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE27D9AF2CFB95FBE4" box="[1016,1051,1106,1130]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="3.5">3.5</number>
Âµm wide, present between larger ducts and narrower ducts; and (iii) narrow ducts, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2765AF08FCE8FB00" box="[836,870,1142,1166]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.5">2.5</number>
â€“3.0 Âµm wide, present throughout. Anal lobes membranous with a well-developed area of sclerotization on inner margin, each with diagonal ridges, each lobe 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE24B6AFC0FF4FFB58" box="[151,193,1214,1238]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="100.0">100</number>
Âµm long; each lobe with a large apical seta, both broken; each inner margin with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20B4AFC0FB2DFB58" box="[1173,1187,1214,1238]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="3.0">3</number>
strongly setose setae towards base, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2552AF9CFE34FB74" box="[371,442,1250,1274]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20â€“23</number>
Âµm long, and 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2641AF9CFDE0FB74" box="[608,622,1250,1274]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
fleshy setae on dorsum nearer apex, more anterior seta 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20C9AF9CFAA0FB74" box="[1256,1326,1250,1274]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12â€“13</number>
Âµm long, more posterior 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2560AE78FEE4FA90" box="[321,362,1286,1310]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8â€“9</number>
Âµm long; ventral surface without a seta near apex but with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE27DFAE78FB82FA90" box="[1022,1036,1286,1310]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
short setose setae (probably medio- and anteroventral setae) more anteriorly, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE268CAE54FD59FACC" box="[685,727,1322,1346]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7â€“8</number>
Âµm long; apparently without an outer margin seta; each lobe with longitudinal lines of about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE25DAAE30FD87FAEB" box="[507,521,1358,1381]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
small 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2672AE33FDD0FAE8" box="[595,606,1357,1382]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.0">8</number>
-shaped pores dorsally and 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE27B0AE30FC11FAE8" box="[913,927,1358,1382]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="6.0">6</number>
ventrally. Median anal plate not visible. Anal ring with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2525AE0CFE9CFA04" box="[260,274,1394,1418]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.0">4</number>
pairs of setae, each about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE261BAE0CFDEDFA04" box="[570,611,1394,1418]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="110.0">110</number>
Âµm long, each narrowing gradually towards apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3411DD581BB0DAC24E6AEE8FE75FECE" lastPageId="146" lastPageNumber="147" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE44E5E81BB0DAC24E6AEE8FE75FECE" blockId="144.[151,1437,565,1958]" lastBlockId="146.[151,1437,151,1149]" lastPageId="146" lastPageNumber="147" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="B92F924C81BB0DAE24E6AEE8FE96FA23" bold="true" box="[199,280,1430,1453]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Venter.</emphasis>
Eight-shaped pores of 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE260BAEE8FDB6FA20" box="[554,568,1430,1454]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
sizes: (i) intermediate-sized pores, similar to those on dorsum, sparse near each antenna, and (ii) small pores, similar to those on dorsum, in radial lines meeting those from dorsum, and also in a more or less semi-circular band submedially; with a few in transverse bands on abdominal segments and on anal lobes. Simple pores, similar to those on dorsum, very sparse. Small bilocular pores, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20F1AD7CFB7CF994" box="[1232,1266,1538,1562]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="3.5">3.5</number>
â€“4.0 x 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2162AD7CFAE8F994" box="[1347,1382,1538,1562]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.5">2.5</number>
Âµm, frequent medially on head and thorax. Spiracular disc-pores small, each 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE27EAAD58FC7BF9B0" box="[971,1013,1574,1598]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4</number>
Âµm wide, those near spiracle usually with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE24EEAD34FF53F9EF" box="[207,221,1610,1633]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
loculi but otherwise with mainly 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2676AD34FDEBF9EF" box="[599,613,1610,1633]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="7.0">7</number>
or 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE26ABAD34FD16F9EC" box="[650,664,1610,1634]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="8.0">8</number>
loculi; posterior band not bifurcated; with very few pores (
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2111AD37FAF9F9EC" box="[1328,1399,1609,1634]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“15</number>
) in each stigmatic band between spiracle and apex, but then forming an almost round apical group on dorsum; numbers in each apex uncertain but probably more than 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2682ADECFD5EF924" box="[675,720,1682,1706]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="100.0">100</number>
; each apical group distinctive as described above under dorsum. Also with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE252FADC8FEDBF940" box="[270,341,1718,1742]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17â€“19</number>
pores, mainly 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE25DEADCBFD85F940" box="[511,523,1717,1742]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
-locular, laterad to each antenna. Multilocular disc-pores, each about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2100ADC8FAA1F940" box="[1313,1327,1718,1742]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="6.0">6</number>
Âµm wide with mainly 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2515ADA4FEDEF97C" box="[308,336,1754,1778]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="10.0">10</number>
loculi, arrangement uncertain but in broad bands on segments Vâ€“VII and apparently just submarginally on segments IVâ€“II and metathorax; perhaps as follows: VIII none; VII with a total about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE216DAD80FAE4F89B" box="[1356,1386,1790,1813]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="75.0">75</number>
, but marginally band appears to turn anteriorly towards segment VI; also with a small group of 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE20BBAC5CFB26F8B4" box="[1178,1192,1826,1850]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="4.0">4</number>
medially between VI and VII; VI band broken but perhaps with a total of about 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE271FAC38FCE9F8D0" box="[830,871,1862,1886]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="115.0">115</number>
disc-pores, plus a submarginal line of 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2109AC38FAB8F8D3" box="[1320,1334,1862,1885]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="5.0">5</number>
between segments VI and V; V with a total of perhaps 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE26B5AC14FD3EF80C" box="[660,688,1898,1922]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="80.0">80</number>
(only visible on one side) and then in submarginal groups, IV with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE24B6ACF0FF5FF828" box="[151,209,1934,1958]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“10</number>
, III &amp; 
<date id="FFE5689E81BB0DAE253DACF0FECAF828" box="[284,324,1934,1958]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
II 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE2517ACF0FECAF828" box="[310,324,1934,1958]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
</date>
on each side, and metathorax with 
<number id="3D935C7981BB0DAE26F0ACF0FD51F828" box="[721,735,1934,1958]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" value="2.0">2</number>
on each side. Tubular ducts similar to narrow 
<typeStatus id="54E0F0FC81BB0DAE20C6ACF0FA99F82B" box="[1255,1303,1934,1957]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">type</typeStatus>
on dorsum, or even slightly narrower; present throughout. Ventral setae slightly more abundant than on dorsum on posterior abdominal segments but all setose and short; preanal setae each 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC27A2ABC2FC11FF5A" box="[899,927,188,212]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="40.0">40</number>
Âµm long; companion setae short. Leg stubs absent. Antennae unsegmented, very short, each about 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC26DAAB9EFC99FF76" box="[763,791,224,248]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="25.0">25</number>
Âµm long and 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC2793AB9EFC40FF76" box="[946,974,224,248]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="25.0">25</number>
Âµm wide, with about 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC20E0AB9EFB41FF76" box="[1217,1231,224,248]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
fleshy setae and 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC21AFAB9EFA12FF76" box="[1422,1436,224,248]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
setose setae; without either an apical cone or a distinct setal cavity. Clypeolabral shield 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC20A7AA7AFB3EFE92" box="[1158,1200,260,284]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="145.0">145</number>
Âµm long. Spiracular peritreme each 
<number id="3D935C7981B90DAC2562AA56FE07FECE" box="[323,393,296,320]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="34.0" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="33.0">33â€“35</number>
Âµm wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
